description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trafford Local Care Organisation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are Trafford Local Care Organisation - an exciting, new public sector organisation bringing together NHS community health services and adult social care services in Trafford. We’re driven by the aim of improving the health of local people in Trafford by working across organisational boundaries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our community healthcare teams in adults and children&#39;s services are employed by Manchester University NHS Foundation Trust and deployed to us, linking closely with our colleagues in Manchester Local Care Organisation. Our teams work as one and together we will make a massive difference to the health of people in Trafford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an excellent opportunity for a newly or recently qualified Speech and Language Therapist to gain experience and skills in a friendly and supportive setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Speech and Language Therapy Service provides;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assessment and intervention for children with speech, language, communication needs and feeding/swallowing disorders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Universal, targeted and specialist training for multi-agency colleagues and parents/ carers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 teams designed around the user’s needs and age&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Children with Special Needs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Children and families in the Community&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Children requiring support in mainstream schools&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Each team is currently professionally managed by a clinical lead SLT and overall by the Team Lead for Speech and Language Therapy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are co-located with teams from Social care, education and health in Sale, Cheshire&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have sessions available in community clinic and mainstream schools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at Sale Waterside, you will be well supported by the Speech and Language Therapy team as well as benefiting from:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Supervision from the management team and specialist staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular team and Professional meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ongoing professional development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent clerical support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive Induction programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
